{{!--
  service-interface.hbs — rendered once per HTTP operation container as the
  service interface that controllers and DI consumers depend on.

  Override via tspconfig.yaml:
    options:
      "@massivescale/tsp-aspnetcore-api":
        templates:
          service-interface: "./templates/service-interface.hbs"

  ── Template variables ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  {{doc}}           — pre-rendered XML <summary> block (may be falsy)

  {{interfaceName}} — service interface name, e.g. "IUsersService"

  {{serviceName}}   — abstract service class name, e.g. "UsersServiceBase"
                      Available for cross-reference comments.

  {{operations}}    — array of operation objects, one per HTTP operation.
                      Each object has:
    .doc            —   pre-rendered XML <summary> block (may be falsy)
    .name           —   PascalCase operation name, e.g. "GetById"
    .httpVerb       —   PascalCase HTTP verb (informational only)
    .routeSuffix    —   relative route fragment (informational only)
    .returnType     —   C# return type from the 2xx response body,
                        e.g. "User", "IList<Widget>", "object"
    .params         —   array of parameter objects.  Each has:
      .name         —     camelCase parameter name
      .type         —     C# type string (non-nullable)
      .binding      —     binding source (informational in service context)
      .optional     —     boolean; true → render type as `{{type}}?`

  {{methodsBlock}}  — shortcut: all operations pre-rendered as
                      `Task<returnType>? nameAsync(params);` declarations
                      (4-space indented) joined by blank lines.

  ── Built-in helpers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  {{indent <text>}}        — 4-space indent on every non-empty line
  {{#if (isDefined val)}}  — true when val is not undefined

  ── Handlebars #each data ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Inside {{#each operations}}:  @index, @first, @last
  Inside {{#each params}}:      @index, @first, @last

  ── Param rendering quick reference ─────────────────────────────────────────

  Service method parameter (no binding attribute):
    {{#if optional}}{{type}}?{{else}}{{type}}{{/if}} {{name}}

  ── Common customisations ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  • Add CancellationToken to every method:
      {{#each operations}}
          Task<{{returnType}}?> {{name}}Async(
              {{#each params}}{{#if optional}}{{type}}?{{else}}{{type}}{{/if}} {{name}},
              {{/each}}CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);
      {{/each}}

  • Use ValueTask instead of Task:
      ValueTask<{{returnType}}?> {{name}}Async(...);

  • Remove the Async suffix:
      Task<{{returnType}}?> {{name}}(...);

  • Add a marker base interface (e.g. IDisposable):
      public interface {{interfaceName}} : IDisposable
--}}
{{#if doc}}{{doc}}
{{/if}}public interface {{interfaceName}}
{
{{#each operations}}{{#if doc}}{{indent doc}}
{{/if}}{{#if (eq returnType "void")}}    Task {{name}}Async({{#each params}}{{#if optional}}{{type}}?{{else}}{{type}}{{/if}} {{name}}{{#unless @last}}, {{/unless}}{{/each}});{{else}}    Task<{{returnType}}?> {{name}}Async({{#each params}}{{#if optional}}{{type}}?{{else}}{{type}}{{/if}} {{name}}{{#unless @last}}, {{/unless}}{{/each}});{{/if}}
{{#unless @last}}

{{/unless}}{{/each}}

}
